  "text": "The Espresso algorithm [CITATION_1] uses a different approach. The returned function is not always the minimal form (but close to it) and the computation is reduced (in both memory and time) by orders of magnitude. It is still heavily used, in particular in the design of logic circuits. Espresso was adapted to deal with multiple-valued logic functions too.",
